The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Sun Micro centre in Chennai

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Aug. 29: Sun Microsystems has opened a global contact centre in Chennai its third in the Asia-Pacific region. The centre can employ up to 300 people.

 The centre has signed up two new clients from India and expects to have 25 by the year-end. It will manage and monitor IT infrastructure and processes like hardware, server, applications and network round the clock and throughout the year.

 The other two centres are located at Ashburn in the US and Linlithgow in Scotland.

 We evaluated capabilities throughout Asia Pacific to determine the best match of skills, language and access to resources to meet our customers requirements and found India to be the perfect match, said Jeya Kumar, vice-president services, Asia Pacific, Sun Microsystems. 




